ame <i>Kari</i> (Old Norse <i>Kári</i>).","Irish: from <b>Ó Ciardha</b>, ‘descendant of <i>Ciardha</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘the black one’."]}]},{"name":"Felicité","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the abstract noun denoting luck or good fortune (via Old French from Latin <i>felicitas</i>;  compare  Felix  ), first used as a given name in the 17th century. It also represents the English form of the Late Latin personal name <i>Felicitas</i>, which was borne by several early saints, notably a slave who was martyred in  203  together with her mistress  Perpetua  and several other companions."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Felicité de Cirey was born from 1187 to 1195, in France, her father, Barthelemy de Cirey, was 30 and her mother, Agnes de Broyes, was 16. She died in 1237."},"et":{"from 1187 to 1195–1237":"1187 kuni 1195–1237","1187–1237":"1187–1237","1190–1237":"1190–1237","1185–Male":"1185–Surnud","1210–1274":"1210–1274","1165–1204":"1165–1204","1180–1219":"1180–1219","1190":"1190","1204":"1204","1237":"1237","1210":"1210","1165":"1165","1187":"1187","1274":"1274","1185":"1185","from 1187 to 1195":"1187 kuni 1195","about 1210":"umbes 1210","1219":"1219","1180":"1180","Rethel, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Rethel, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"from 1187 to 1195–1237":"vuodesta 1187 vuoteen 1195–1237","1187–1237":"1187–1237","1190–1237":"1190–1237","1185–Male":"1185–Kuollut","1210–1274":"1210–1274","1165–1204":"1165–1204","1180–1219":"1180–1219","1190":"1190","1204":"1204","1237":"1237","1210":"1210","1165":"1165","1187":"1187","1274":"1274","1185":"1185","from 1187 to 1195":"vuodesta 1187 vuoteen 1195","about 1210":"noin 1210","1219":"1219","1180":"1180","Rethel, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Rethel, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, Ranska","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"from 1187 to 1195–1237":"du 1187 au 1195–1